Description: Jennifer programming language interpreter
 Jennifer is a small, experimental, interpreted programming language.
 Source files use the .j extension.
 .
 This package installs two binaries:
   * /usr/bin/jennifer    - TinyGo build (canonical, small, embeddable)
   * /usr/bin/jennifer-go - standard Go build (performance variant)
 .
 Both binaries share the same source and language; only the compiler
 differs. jennifer is the default; jennifer-go is the right choice
 for compute-bound code where the size delta doesn't matter.
 .
 The .j extension is registered as text/x-jennifer so file managers
 and editors recognise Jennifer source files.
